<subSubSection id="255D3FFF53AAE2BDEB5DA006B68B9BCA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="C5A045FDB1696280184422861C6040B3" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="17A9DE372E975C678CDE934B34D782D4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Suffruticose plant, forming dense mats or hummocks, with rhizome-like stems up to 17 cm long covered with matted lanate indumentum and leaf bases, rather erect, simple or branched from the base. 
<emphasis id="C79F439044D336307FB52986EACEDEB0" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Stems</emphasis>
1.5-4 cm tall (aerial part), lanate. 
<emphasis id="C16CB7CB22B6D003BDCC2DE2D7EE27FB" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Leaves</emphasis>
stellate-imbricate, extending into a sheath-like base that bears long silky trichomes, usually with the leaf lamina spreading at nearly 90° from the sheath-like base; leaf laminas 6.5-27.6 
<normalizedToken id="3D6A05F46DC18504B1381FCA28549617" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.2-2.2 mm, linear, obtuse, usually callous-like tipped at the apex, entire, flat to elliptical in cross section, glabrous, 1-nerved above, 1-nerved beneath, fleshy, matte or shiny. 
<emphasis id="88F58D5547A1221238754BFD761C516E" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Capitula</emphasis>
radiate, erect, sessile to subsessile (rarely with a short peduncle up to 8 mm long). 
<emphasis id="5214510E64C5260082582B23B14061EC" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Involucres</emphasis>
10.2-19.7 
<normalizedToken id="F509A9240A305DEE491EB272DDDFBBA6" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7.8-15.8 mm, cupuliform; involucral bracts 11 to 21, 6-14.9 
<normalizedToken id="30F0BE20D511DEE3220CE6D78DB53C9F" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.6-2.2 mm, rather acute at the apex, greenish to dark-purplish. 
<emphasis id="575ECDF26CC0998B3269B431BF7C9BBB" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ray florets</emphasis>
13 to 21; corollas 13-19.7 
<normalizedToken id="8C2A1C8779E0026CCB686136B7B8E9CE" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.7-3.4 mm, 4 to 6-veined, subentire to 3-toothed at the apex, conspicuously surpassing the involucre, white. 
<emphasis id="A13EA3EE3253311FF9F8FE6DDE06292D" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Disc florets</emphasis>
50 to 95; corollas 6.6-8.1 mm long, yellow; style branches truncate with a crown of sweeping trichomes, yellowish, purple-tipped. 
<emphasis id="04547EA859F7ED93A24767962B19899D" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Achenes</emphasis>
2.6-4 
<normalizedToken id="CB2BBE56485624E50251EC18C60AD153" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.8-1 mm, cylindrical, 6 to 8-ribbed, glabrous; pappus 7.8-19 mm long, barbellate, whitish. Chromosome number unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B010D13F1F5B81E5DAA50C272E197BC9" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="8071A73FC78DF05B9604B27671ECE811" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E69C3BFAAFC1F61C000B14CBDECA626E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation id="1EC9DFA54DD56435E15420E64AB38B98" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/3391934" author="Funk, VA" journalOrPublisher="Novon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="235 - 241" refId="B15" refString="Funk, VA, 1997a. Xenophyllum, a New Andean Genus Extracted from Werneria s.l. (Compositae: Senecioneae). Novon 7 (3): 235 - 241, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/3391934" title="Xenophyllum, a New Andean Genus Extracted from Werneria s. l. (Compositae: Senecioneae)." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3391934" volume="7" year="1997 a">Funk (1997a)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the holotype of the name 
<taxonomicName id="73F42310ABB21D33E01C3B0FE1464ACC" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="1928" class="Amphibia" family="Bufonidae" genus="Werneria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Werneria crassa" order="Anura" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassa">
<emphasis id="B70000ED1A3EF42F473A8E093CBC604E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Werneria crassa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
S.F.Blake (US-1141291) may had been destroyed while on loan to B, and accordingly, she designated the duplicate at K as the lectotype (
<bibRefCitation id="D6A5576225E07BAD7B5E351F6ADCBFE5" DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B33" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, W-H, Li, D-Z, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prado, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF, 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code). Regnum Vegetabile 159: I-XXXVIII, 1-254. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code). Regnum Vegetabile 159: I-XXXVIII, 1 - 254." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
, ICN Art. 9.3).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
